## Fix Summary

All 7 tasks complete. Here's what was diagnosed and fixed:

### Root Cause
The CTEM swarm orchestrator (`run-ctem-swarm.sh`) was invoking Claude CLI **without the `--agent` flag** at line ~4157, unlike both `run-ai-team.sh` and `run-ai-team-unleashed.sh` which correctly pass it. This caused the CLI to not load agent persona, model, or permission configurations from the `.md` frontmatter, resulting in 0-byte output for all 17 agents. A secondary issue was unbounded prompt growth (75KB observed) from accumulated retry/SCP context.

### Fixes Applied
| # | Fix | File | Lines |
|---|-----|------|-------|
| 1 | Added `--agent "$agent_name"` to CLI invocation | `run-ctem-swarm.sh` | ~4185 |
| 2 | Added 50KB prompt size cap | `run-ctem-swarm.sh` | ~4164-4171 |
| 3 | Added stale `.prompt.tmp` cleanup in pre-flight | `run-ctem-swarm.sh` | ~3350-3356 |
| 4 | Updated vision-agent status to reflect actual output | `vision-agent-status.md` | full rewrite |

### Verification
- Syntax check passes (`/opt/homebrew/bin/bash -n` = 0)
- 2 stale prompt.tmp files cleaned (146KB freed)
- Fix report written to `.claude/team-state/fix-vision-agent-status.md`

### Key Insight
The vision-agent was actually the **most productive agent** today (7 artifacts, 7 decisions, Grade A in its own health assessment). The "D" persona grade was misleading — it only checked log output size (0B) rather than the real artifacts the agent produced (`vision-alignment-*.json`, `vision-preflight-*.md`, `sprint-board.json` updates).
